gomodel:SYNGO_1202  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5. KA2 (Kainate receptor subunit) measured with western blot in pre- and post-synaptic fractions (note that while detected presynaptically, it was enriched in postsynaptic fraction).\n\n8/9/2017 Pim\n- Experiments involve quantification of plasma membrane/surface levels of receptors via biotinylation assay.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Slices 400 lm thick were prepared from cortex and hippocampi of adult Wistar rats" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
